      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Price of Gas, Here and There</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>J Bradford Harlow Jr letter says Americans expect cheap gas (July 2 article) because it has always been cheap</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Life, Liberty, Cheap Gas'' (letter, July 2): The simple answer as to why Americans expect cheap gas is that it always has been cheap. People pay high prices for gold, lobsters and Mercedes-Benzes because they expect to. Imagine the flap if bread suddenly cost $5 a loaf.</p>
        <p>J. BRADFORD HARLOW JR.  Enfield, N.H., July 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
